Hello,

Our team is using a NEO Vortex swerve drive with CANcoder encoders. We’ve been trying to program it for over a month now, but we’re still having trouble and really want to get our robot moving soon. We’re struggling to find a program template specifically for the NEO Vortex swerve drive.

Does anyone have a plug-and-play-ish NEO Vortex swerve drive program?

Any additional tips or instructions on how to adjust the code for our robot would also be super helpful.

Thank you!
EVE Robotics ,Team 7514

I heartily recommend looking into YAGSL as well.

Our adoption was slightly rocky because we (initially) refused to carefully read and follow the docs and flowchart for bring-up. That 3 days of labor in the lab was in an attempt to save us 90 minutes of carefully following the instructions. Once we did that, it’s been a great experience.

Looks like 3624 is using Vortexes (though using thrifty encoders). We’re using CANcoders but legacy Neos with SparkMax. (I can’t guarantee the state of our current code, but our fall 2024 off-season bot code should be stable and work out of the box [at least a little bit/enough to get you started]).
